:R-HSA-9020265  a           obo:GO_0042759 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The D-series resolvins (RvD1-6) are biosynthesised from the precursor ω-3 fatty acid docosahexaenoic acid (DHA), either via the lipoxygenase pathway (17(S)-RvDs) or via aspirin-triggered cylcooxygenase catalysis (described here) forming the epimeric 17(R)-RvD1-6 resolvins (Serhan et al. 2014, Bannenberg & Serhan 2010)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Biosynthesis of aspirin-triggered D-series resolvins" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Hansen, Trond Vidar, 2018-02-21" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2017-09-05" , "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2017-09-05" ;
